description: Creates a new Timestream database. If the KMS key is not specified, the database will be encrypted with a Timestream managed KMS key located in your account. For more information, see Amazon Web Services managed keys. Service quotas apply. For details, see code sample.

parameters.name: DatabaseName
parameters.description: The name of the Timestream database.

parameters.name: Tags
parameters.description: A list of key-value pairs to label the table. (dict) --- A tag is a label that you assign to a Timestream database and/or table. Each tag consists of a key and an optional value, both of which you define. With tags, you can categorize databases and/or tables, for example, by purpose, owner, or environment. The key of the tag. Tag keys are case sensitive. The value of the tag. Tag values are case-sensitive and can be null.

nested_params.name: Key
nested_params.description: The key of the tag. Tag keys are case sensitive.

nested_params.name: Value
nested_params.description: The value of the tag. Tag values are case-sensitive and can be null.

nested_items.name: Arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name that uniquely identifies this database.

nested_items.name: DatabaseName
nested_items.description: The name of the Timestream database.

nested_items.name: TableCount
nested_items.description: The total number of tables found within a Timestream database.

nested_items.name: KmsKeyId
nested_items.description: The identifier of the KMS key used to encrypt the data stored in the database.

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: The time when the database was created, calculated from the Unix epoch time.

nested_items.name: LastUpdatedTime
nested_items.description: The last time that this database was updated.
